<br>
Humanity is going to mutate over time. Thats too strong a word really. We will change. Even as little as 2000 years ago we were averaging 4 feet in height but surprisingly tough and strong. A centurion for example carried very heavy packs on long marches which would put our modern armies to shame. In the Time Machine the Eloi were unchanged. despite 800,000 years. This is not how the original tale went. It didn't have such a happy ending either.<br>
<br>
I could imagine 20th century humans spread across the millenia as they explore the universe in lightspeed ships. Crossing paths and meeting up with one another. It would be fascinating to be constantly meeting peoples of different times. You might agree to meet some friends at a star 20,000 years distant. You both take different directions to explore different stop off points along the way but arrange the journeys to coincide at the target star. You could all get home 40,000 years later having only spent a subjective time of a few years in space. Whole Worlds would have been colonised in that time. New nations developed, wars raged, new technologies invented. Immortality would likely be possible and the human race would still be around because it wouldn't be confined to Earth. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<br>Nuclear power is the next logical step for serious space travel. The technology required to colonise the solar system exists now!

